PURPOSE:

[
 The purpose of this project is to apply the design patterns/principle and build a multi-threaded chat service.
]

PERCENT COMPLETE:

[
  I believe I have completed 100% of this project.
]

PARTS THAT ARE NOT COMPLETE:

[
 None.
]

BUGS:

[
 None.
]

FILES:

[
  Included with this project are 12 files:
  
  build.xml, the ANT xml file
  README.txt, the project text file you are presently reading
  src/chat/client/ClientDriver.java, main ClientDriver class file for client
  src/chat/client/ClientWorker.java, Worker class for client side
  src/chat/driver/MainDriver.java, MainDriver class which will be called
  src/chat/server/ServerDriver.java, ServerDriver class file for server side
  src/chat/server/ServerHandler.java, ServerHandler file for client connection
  src/chat/server/ServerWorker.java, Worker class for server side
  src/chat/server/ThreadInfo.java, ThreadInfo file toe save the thread information
  src/chat/util/Logger.java, Logger class to implement the BACKUP
  src/chat/util/ThreadPool.java, ThreadPool file to manage threads
  src/chat/util/Worker.java, Worker interface file

 
]

SAMPLE OUTPUT:

[
	Sample output for 1 client and 1 server.
	commands used: ./run server 6790 and ./run localhost 6790
	**ServerMenu**
	1)Send Message to specific client
	2)Print Message from specific client
	3)Quit
	Select your choice:
	2
	Enter client ID:
	1
	client1:hello

	
	**ClientMenu**
	1)Give me a name
	2)Send Message to server
	3)Print Message from server
	4)Quit
	Select your choice:
	1
	Enter Name:
	client1
	Select your choice:
	2
	Enter your message:
	hello



]

TO COMPILE:

[
  Please extract the tar file, go to the directory Chaitanya_Bhasme_assign2 and do-> ant compile
]

TO RUN:

[
  Please go the the extracted directory Chaitanya_Bhasme_assign2 and do-> chmod +x run.sh
  run as: ./run.sh server <PORT_ID> and ./run.sh client <IP_ADDRESS> <PORT_ID>
  For example: ./run.sh server 6790 and ./run.sh client localhost 6790
]

